            <title>Amazon Is Shutting Down The Wondery App</title>
            <description>Amazon is shuttering its Wondery app for podcasts and its Wondery+
                subscription
                service. </description>
            <dc:creator>Mary Whitfill Roeloffs, Forbes Staff</dc:creator>
            <atom:author>
                <atom:name>Mary Whitfill Roeloffs, Forbes Staff</atom:name>
                <atom:uri>https://www.forbes.com/sites/maryroeloffs/</atom:uri>
            </atom:author>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">content_69a73b9be2084e142c019a06</guid>
            <pubDate>Tue, 03 Mar 2026 15:00:48 -0500</pubDate>
            <atom:updated>2026-03-03T15:00:48-05:00</atom:updated>
            <content:encoded>&lt;h2 class="topline-heading"&gt;Topline&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Amazon
                will keep
                its most popular podcasts on the audio book app Audible but will close its Wondery
                app and
                the Wondery+ subscription service months after the podcast network laid off 100
                workers in a
                reorganization last year. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img
                src="https://specials-images.forbesimg.com/imageserve/69a73d9b29d87c8dd1a6cabc/960x0.jpg?cropX1=0&amp;amp;cropX2=1576&amp;amp;cropY1=81&amp;amp;cropY2=967"
                alt="In this photo illustration, the Wondery logo is
                seen..."&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Wondery logo.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;small&gt;SOPA
                Images/LightRocket via Getty
                Images&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Key
                Facts&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;div
                class="key-facts"&gt;&lt;div class="key-facts-element"&gt;&lt;p&gt;In a note to
                users
                Tuesday, Amazon said both the Wondery+ app and subscription service will no longer
                be
                available in the coming months, and directed listeners instead to Audible, the
                audiobook app
                it acquired in 2008.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div
                class="key-facts-element"&gt;&lt;p&gt;The
                Wondery podcast network, which was purchased by Amazon Music in 2020, is home to
                some of the
                most popular podcasts on the market like "How I Built This with Guy Raz," "New
                Heights” and
                “Armchair Expert.”&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div
                class="key-facts-element"&gt;&lt;p&gt;The
                Wondery brand will continue to produce the popular shows, but not on its own
                dedicated app.
                &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="key-facts-element"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This
                is a
                developing story and will be updated. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content:encoded>
